===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[astronomia]]''', from Greek '''[[ἄστρον]]''', ''star'', +   '''[[νόμος]]''', ''law'', + suffix '''[[-ία]]''' (literally ''law of the stars'').

===Noun===
'''astronomy'''

#The study of the [[physical]] [[universe]] beyond the Earth's [[atmosphere]], and in particular the process of [[mapping]] [[location]] and [[properties]] of the [[matter]] and [[radiation]] in the universe. The study of the physical processes which control physical bodies in the universe is commonly called [[astrophysics]]. The physical description of the properties of the universe itself is called [[cosmology]].

